    },
    "body": "`NodeClockContext` was introduced in #34479  as a small RAII helper for tests and fuzz targets: it sets mock node time on construction and resets the global mock time on destruction. The motivation there was to make mock-time usage less error-prone and to avoid mock time leaking from one fuzz input to the next.\r\n\r\nAll current in-tree uses of NodeClockContext pass an explicit time, e.g.\r\n\r\n```c++\r\nNodeClockContext clock_ctx{ConsumeTime(fuzzed_data_provider)};\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe no-argument constructor is not used anywhere.",
